>>docker run ubuntu  cat /etc/*release* ,will run container and give version of ubuntu

(tag)
>>docker run ubuntu:17.04 cat /etc/*release*,will run ubuntu version 17.04
first it will find that image available locally if not then will pull and run .

--------
>>docker run ubuntu sleep 15 ,application is just sleep command 
will not come out before 15 sec.

(detached mode)
>>docker run -d ubuntu sleep 1500 
(container will run in background ,come out of terminal)

(attach mode)
>>docker attach containerId,again will go into docker container running terminal

>>docker run timer,
>>docker run -d timer 
>>docker ps 
>>docker attach containerId
(again will show in terminal)

---------
>>docker run jenkins
(how to access the web ui)

>>docker ps ,will show internal ip of jenkins container
or
>>docker inspect ConId 

go to web and type ip:port ,will open ui

externally access ...
ip of docker host.

>>docker run -p 8080:8080 jenkins 

now can access. using system ip.

(ip of container,within docker host) outside docker host cann't access
(ip of dockerhost)

-------
(persisting data)

>>mkdir my-jenkins-data

>>docker run -p 8080:8080 -v /root/my-jenkins-data:/var/jenkins_home -u root jenkins

(when again open container after stopping ,it will take data from local)

----docker run --name prashant ubuntu,renaming the container.